article.headline: Binghamton 59, New Hampshire 53
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Brandon Carter scored 15 points, including two 3-pointers in the decisive run, and Binghamton beat New Hampshire 59-53 on Saturday. Carter sandwiched his 3s around a jumper by Alex Adediran in an 8-1 run that gave the Bearcats (12-13, 8-6 America East) a 49-42 lead with 6 minutes remaining. Ben Sturgill had 12 points for New Hampshire (6-18, 2-12), which got as close as 51-48 with 1:56 remaining. Troy Hailey and Billy Williams each had 10 points for Binghamton. Freshman Blagoj Janov added 10 points for the Wildcats.
